;>

Hark-store only has a couple of subscription paths: One for new notifications,
and one for all updates.

Only the local ship or its moons can subscribe to these paths.

# `/notes`

New notifications are sent out on this path.

These updates will have a `%hark-update` mark and contain an
[`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) structure
with an [`%add-note`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#-add-note-)
tag.

---

# `/updates`

All updates of any kind are sent out on this path.

These updates will have a %hark-update mark and contain an
[`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) structure of
any kind.

Upon first subscribing to this path, `%hark-store` will give you an initial
state. It will contain a
[`%more`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#-more-)
[`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) containing:

- A [`%timebox`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#-timebox-)
  [`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) with an
  %unseen [`+$lid`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#lid-),
  containing all unseen notifications.

- A [`%timebox`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#-timebox-)
  [`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) with a
  %seen [`+$lid`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#lid-),
  containing all seen notifications.

- An [`%all-stats`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#-all-stats-)
  [`+$update`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#update-) containing
  statistics for all
  [`+$place`](/~/scry/docs/dev/garden/hark-store/types.html#place-)s.
